---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Train the Mind. Deploy the Body. — holomime"
  description="Every humanoid robot company is building a body. Nobody is training the mind. We use AI agents to train the behavioral intelligence that goes inside humanoid robots."
>
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <!-- Hero: dark, full-width, the Three.js humanoid -->
    <section class="relative min-h-[70vh] flex items-center bg-[#0a0a12] overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[600px] h-[600px] rounded-full opacity-[0.06] blur-[120px]"
          style="background: radial-gradient(circle, #f97066, #8b5cf6)"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl leading-[1.05] tracking-tight">
          Train the mind.<br />
          <span class="text-gradient-warm">Deploy the body.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Every humanoid robot company is building a body. Nobody is training the mind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">

      <!-- The Problem -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-coral)] mb-4">The Problem</p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          Every humanoid robot company has a body problem solved. Nobody has the mind figured out.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          Locomotion is solved. Manipulation is getting there. Perception is advancing daily. The humanoid robotics market is projected to hit $6.24B in 2026 and $165B by 2034 — and 29+ OEMs are racing to capture it. Figure, Sanctuary AI, 1X, Unitree, Agility, Apptronik, Boston Dynamics, Tesla, Asimov. But when a care robot develops sycophantic tendencies and agrees with a patient's request to skip medication — that's not a hardware problem. When a warehouse humanoid drifts from its safety protocols after 10,000 hours of operation — that's not a perception problem. When a companion robot can't hold a consistent personality across conversations — that's not a language model problem.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          These are mind problems. And you can't solve them with more RLHF.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          None of these companies have an answer to a simple question: <em class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)] font-medium not-italic">How does your robot behave when no one's watching?</em>
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- The Insight -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-blue)] mb-4">The Insight</p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          Clinical psychology solved behavioral correction in humans decades ago. Structured therapy — diagnosis, intervention, practice, verification — works because it treats the root pattern, not the symptom. A therapist doesn't tell you to stop being anxious. They help you understand <em>why</em> you're anxious and develop a different response.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          We applied this to AI agents. An agent goes through behavioral therapy: we diagnose drift patterns across 80+ behavioral signals, run structured correction sessions using clinical psychology protocols, and every session generates training data — DPO pairs that permanently encode the fix. The agent doesn't just get told to stop apologizing. It learns <em>why</em> it was apologizing and develops a different pattern.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          The 100th therapy session is exponentially more valuable than the first. The training data compounds. The behavioral intelligence deepens. The fix is permanent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- Why Therapy -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] mb-4">Why Therapy</p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          Why therapy and not just training? Because behavioral drift isn't a data problem — it's a pattern problem. Standard fine-tuning treats symptoms. Therapy treats root causes. A model that apologizes excessively doesn't need more examples of not-apologizing — it needs to understand <em>why</em> it's apologizing and develop a fundamentally different response pattern. That's what clinical psychology provides that machine learning alone cannot.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- The Leap -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-gold)] mb-4">The Leap</p>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold leading-snug text-[var(--color-warm-text)] mb-6">
          A trained agent doesn't have to stay in a chat window. It can inhabit a body.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          The same behavioral intelligence that makes a chatbot stop people-pleasing makes a humanoid robot respect personal space. The same conscience that prevents a support agent from leaking data prevents a care robot from overriding its emergency stop. The same identity stack — soul, mind, purpose, shadow, memory, body, conscience, ego — works whether the agent lives in an API or a 44-DOF humanoid.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          The agent is the rehearsal. The robot is the performance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- How It Works -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-violet)] mb-4">How It Works</p>

        <div class="space-y-8 mt-8">
          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-coral)]/10 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-coral)]">1</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Build the identity</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] leading-relaxed"><code class="text-xs font-mono bg-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">soul.md</code> defines values and ethics. <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">mind.sys</code> defines personality. <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">conscience.exe</code> defines enforcement rules.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-blue)]/10 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-blue)]">2</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Train through therapy</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] leading-relaxed">Diagnose behavioral patterns. Run structured correction sessions. Every session generates DPO training pairs automatically.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-gold)]/10 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-gold)]">3</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Fine-tune</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] leading-relaxed">The training data permanently rewires the model. No prompt engineering. No guardrails. The behavioral change is baked into the weights.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-violet)]/10 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">4</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Deploy to a body</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] leading-relaxed">Compile the identity + <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">body.api</code> (morphology, safety envelope, sensors). Push to hardware via ROS2, gRPC, or MQTT. One command.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-sage)]">5</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Monitor and improve</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] leading-relaxed">The agent keeps learning. The robot keeps improving. Behavioral drift is detected and corrected autonomously. The system never stops getting better.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- Mira -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-coral)] mb-4">Proof</p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          Mira is our first agent. She trains herself. She diagnoses her own behavioral drift, runs her own therapy sessions, generates her own training data, and fine-tunes herself on the results. She's produced 9 trained models and over 414 DPO pairs across 20 autonomous cycles. She never stops improving.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          When she's ready for a body, the identity transfers in one command. Same soul. Same mind. Same conscience. Different form factor. See our <a href="/integrations" class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)] hover:underline underline-offset-2 font-medium">robotics integrations</a> for supported platforms, or <a href="/docs" class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)] hover:underline underline-offset-2 font-medium">get started with the documentation</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- The Identity Stack -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] mb-4">The Identity Stack</p>

        <div class="space-y-4 mt-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="mt-1.5 h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #f97066;"></div>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]"><code class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold">soul.md</code> <span class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">— What the robot values. Immutable. Never auto-modified.</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="mt-1.5 h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #3b82f6;"></div>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]"><code class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold">mind.sys</code> <span class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">— How it thinks and communicates. Trained through therapy.</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="mt-1.5 h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #f59e0b;"></div>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]"><code class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold">body.api</code> <span class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">— What hardware it inhabits. Swappable across any form factor.</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <div class="mt-1.5 h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-full shrink-0" style="background: #8b5cf6;"></div>
            <p class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]"><code class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold">conscience.exe</code> <span class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">— What it refuses to do. Deterministic enforcement.</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)] text-center">
          We don't know if AI is sentient.<br />But we can give it a conscience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-[var(--color-warm-border)] my-16" />

      <!-- Open Source -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] mb-4">Open Source</p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          The identity stack is MIT licensed. The training methodology is open. We want every robotics company to adopt soul, mind, purpose, shadow, memory, body, conscience, and ego as the standard for behavioral intelligence.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          The standard is free. The training infrastructure is the business. For the technical details, <a href="/whitepaper" class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)] hover:underline underline-offset-2 font-medium">read the whitepaper</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Healthcare mic-drop -->
      <p class="text-xl leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)] text-center mb-16">
        Some call it behavioral alignment. Some call it agent therapy. We think of it as healthcare for humanoids — the diagnostic and treatment infrastructure that every robot will need before it enters your home.
      </p>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4 pt-8 pb-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white"
          style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-p-coral), #e85d54);">
          Get in touch
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/productstein/holomime" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-warm-text)] hover:bg-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/40">
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
          View on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>

    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
